'''Fiľakovské Kováče''' ({{lang-hu|Fülekkovácsi}}) is a village and municipality in the [[Lučenec District]] in the [[Banská Bystrica Region]] of [[Slovakia]].

==History==
In [[history|historical records]], the [[village]] was first mentioned in 1246 (1246 ''Cuach'', 1295 ''Koachy'', 1454 ''Kowachy''). It belonged to Fil’akovo town. In 1548 it was destroyed by [[Ottoman Empire|Turks]]. From 1938 to 1945 it belonged to [[Hungary]].

